==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shower
<hw>Show"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
shows or exhibits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which shows; a mirror.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shower</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Shower
<hw>Show"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>shour</ets>,
<ets>schour</ets>, AS. <ets>se<?/r</ets>; akin to D. <ets>schoer</ets>,
G. <ets>schauer</ets>, OHG. <ets>sc<?/r</ets>, Icel. <ets>sk<?/r</ets>,
Sw. <ets>skur</ets>, Goth. <ets>sk<?/ra windis</ets> a storm of wind; of
uncertain origin.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fall or rain or hail of
short duration; sometimes, but rarely, a like fall of snow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In drought or else <qex>showers</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or wet the thirsty earth with falling <qex>showers</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which resembles a shower in falling or passing
through the air copiously and rapidly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>showers</qex> of stones he drives them far away.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A copious supply bestowed.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He and myself⟦br⟧
Have travail'd in the great <qex>shower</qex> of your gifts.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Shower bath</b></col>, <cd>a bath in which water is
showered from above, and sometimes from the sides also.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shower</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Shower
<hw>Show"er</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Showered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Showering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To water with a
shower; to wet copiously with rain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest it again dissolve and <qex>shower</qex> the earth.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bestow liberally; to distribute or scatter in
abundance; to rain.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Caesar's favor,⟦br⟧
That <qex>showers</qex> down greatness on his friends.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shower</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Shower
<hw>Show"er</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To rain in showers; to fall, as
in a shower or showers.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Showerful</ent>⟦br⟧
